    "privileged_info_summary": "The task uses real NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis Derived surface air temperature data (air.mon.ltm.nc). The briefing request incorrectly states that the data is in Kelvin and instructs the user to use 273.15 K as the freezing threshold. However, inspection of the NetCDF file reveals that the 'air' variable is in degrees Celsius ('degC'). The correct freezing threshold to plot is therefore 0\u00b0C, not 273.15. Data analysis of the target basin (42-52N, 114-122W) shows February is almost entirely sub-freezing, March sees the onset of melting with 7/15 grid cells exceeding 0\u00b0C, and April sees widespread melting (11/15 cells).",
